This is an introduction to the MyHDL hardware description language.
It is based on a number of examples that illustrates many important
aspects of MyHDL. The idea is to go through the examples in number order
and read all the comments in the example. Run the examples and view
the output from them.

Prerequisites are that you install these packages:
Must install:
  python3
  gtkwave
Recommended:
  yosys
  iverilog
  netlistsvg (intall npm then: npm install -g netlistsvg)

The examples are in the intro directory.

